{
  "texts": [
    "However, the durations of different action instances are different, and it is impossible to find a receptive field that fits every time.",
    "Similar to TAL-Net's multiscale receptive field, Gong et al.",
    "proposed TSA-Net in 2019, which uses a set of parameterized time convolution modules called multi-dilation temporal convolution blocks (MDCs) to handle all timescales.",
    "The model design is similar to (Lin et al. 2018; Chao et al. 2018) but is fundamentally different when simultaneously dealing with multiple timescales.",
    "To address the low accuracy of the boundary-based approach, TSA-Net detects three types of points simultaneously: the start point, the endpoint, and the midpoint of the action instance."
  ]
}